<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4960] race condition in CoreContainer.shutdown leads to double closes on cores</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4960</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;CoreContainer.shutdown has a race condition that can lead to a closed (or closing) core being handed out to an incoming request.  This can further lead to SolrCore.close() logic being executed again when the request is finished.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bug was introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4196&quot; title=&quot;Untangle XML-specific nature of Config and Container classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4196&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4196&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; r1451797&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12654747">SOLR-4960</key>
            <summary>race condition in CoreContainer.shutdown leads to double closes on cores</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
